{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #625: declared status 'open'. Formalized: no. The cochromatic number of $G$, denoted by $\\zeta(G)$, is the minimum number of colours needed to colour the vertices of $G$ such that each colour class induces either a complete graph or empty graph. Let $\\chi(G)$ denote the chromatic number.\n\nIf $G$ is a random graph with $n$ vertices and each edge included independently with probability $1/2$ then is it true that almost surely\\[\\chi(G) - \\zeta(G) \\to \\infty\\]as $n\\to \\infty$? Current best: It is known that almost surely\\[\\frac{n}{2\\log_2n}\\leq \\zeta(G)\\leq \\chi(G)\\leq (1+o(1))\\frac{n}{2\\log_2n}.\\](The final upper bound is due to Bollob\\'{a}s \\cite{Bo88}. Prize: $1000. Tags: chromatic number, graph theory.","id":"vf_a5108d3535e26a37","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: FC 625 (PR #570) [in-pr] https://github.com/google-deepmind/formal-conjectures/pull/570.","id":"vf_ea6f9a18363ffcd1","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/625.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_a5108d3535e26a37","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:625","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_ea6f9a18363ffcd1","source_root":"sha256:540d4967071425f77c693e61f62053208b07d67667490dcb9eeef62ec3f1d316","target":"erdos:625","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_ea6f9a18363ffcd1","source_root":"sha256:540d49670714